30/09/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Representatives of the EU, NATO and OSCE voiced concern Wednesday (29 September) regarding the November referendum on the controversial new decentralisation laws and possible repercussions. 
At a joint news conference, the international officials warned that the referendum was already delaying progress achieved by the state and could further jeopardise the Euro-Atlantic integration process.
Meanwhile, NATO Force Planning Department's Director Frank Boland wrapped up a visit to Skopje on Wednesday. 
He praised progress achieved in the area of defence reforms. 
(Utrinski Vesnik - 30/09/04; Makfax, A1 TV - 29/09/04)
